midpoint a
Both operands have to be extremely large to cause overflow.
I used inputs 2147483647 and -2147483647. It failed because 2147483647 is Ob 0111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 and -2147483647 is Ob 1000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0001 so the midpoint is expected to be 0.

However, midpoint_a failed when it computes y - x

  Ob 1000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0001
-
  Ob 0111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111
--------------------------------------------
     0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0010

2 / 2 = 1 or 1

ob 0111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111
+
                                         1 
------------------------------------------
   1000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000

= -2147483648

midpoint b
Both operands have to be negative to cause overflow.
I used inputs -4 and -4. It failed because -4 = 0b 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1100.

0b 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1100
+
0b 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1100
-------------------------------------------
0b 1 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1000
                                        >1
0b 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1111 1100 = -2147483644
